Address: Lot 22 Grantville-Glen Alvie Road Grantville VIC 3984
Description:
Under Contract - Final Stage of Eastern Shores
Lot 22 Grantville-Glen Alvie Road, 743 m2
Eastern Shores Estate last and FINAL land release is underway with Titles expected early 2018. The land enjoys views towards the sea and the woodland nature reserve next to the estate. Land sizes vary and the land whilst mostly flat has some elevated lots which will capture views. This is the final stage of land release in Grantville at present so get in early to secure your lot. Eastern Shores is located minutes stroll away from all the shops and services in Grantville which include a Post Office, Newsagency, Council Offices, Medical Centre, Ambulance station and Chemist. There are a number of Cafes and fast food outlets and a Bakery. Grantville is approx. 20 mins from San Remo, 30 mins from Wonthaggi and Cowes and approx. 35 mins from Cranbourne and Pakenham. There is an excellent new Early Childhood campus beside the popular Bass Valley Primary School and there are multiple Secondary School options in the locality. A V- Line Bus runs regularly to Melbourne and beyond into Gippsland. The township is growing rapidly but land is running out just as fast!
Deposit of $500 is due upon signing contracts with the balance of 10% deposit within 21 days. The balance will be due within 14 days of the Titles being issued by the Land Titles office.
Contact Liz Leahy for more information on 0487 022 099

Description:
HOT PROPERTY - GRANTVILLE 2604 m2
With unprecedented sales, Grantville is fast becoming the go to town for buyers of new homes and this property offers all the must haves, on beach side, Titled and ready to build on and space, all 2604 m2 of it!
This fabulous Titled block is located across the road from the shopping precinct in Grantville. On the corner of Bass Highway and Wheatley Court and just a stroll onto the sand at the foreshore, the location couldnt be more perfect. There is a reserve at the rear so no neighbours and an open green outlook awaits with tracks through the foreshore area, you can walk the dog for miles. Possible sea views from a double storey design await.
With approx 2604 m2 to play with this could be the dream block for your next home or get creative and plan a unit development or simply sub-divide into smaller lots.
Buyers are crying out for Titled land in Grantville and theres very little available. This block could represent your financial future, buy it with your Super Fund or do a joint venture with a builder to develop, the possibilities abound.

Description:
MONOMEITH PARK - SIGNIFICANT HOLDING ON MELBOURNE DOORSTEP.
Investors and graziers take note of this historical 565 acre property. Retirement beckons for the Bourke family and for the first time in its long history, Monomeith Park a unique, superb holding in the highly regarded Monomeith/Caldermeade area goes to the market.
Key features of Monomeith Park:
• Rare holding, 565 acres, 3 titles, only 85 kms. from Melbourne,
• Impressive, heritage listed homestead, original stables, outbuildings,
• Renowned beef fattening and dairy country, reliable rainfall,
• Water security, storage dam, 5 bores, windmills, troughs,
• Location ideal for a large scale professional equine enterprise,
• Versatile, with outstanding appeal to international interests,
• Massive potential for eco-tourism ventures, farm stay, horse etc.
For further information please contact: RAY CULLEN: 0429 977313. PAT REDDAN: 0418 310 866

Description:
Contemporary Home On a Huge Block!
Contemporary home consists of large kitchen/meals, lounge with an adjoining dining room, three good sized bedrooms, big bathroom, separate laundry and toilet. The house has timber floors, large reverse cycle air conditioner, gas stove and rangehood. There are views to Westernport from the front deck. The land area is in excess of 2600 square metres and is fully fenced it has two separate double gate access to the yard which has a massive shed with carport entrance and a sleepout like room at the back. There is another low profile open ended double shed at the top of the property and in the back yard is an old chook house. This property has plenty of room to park large trucks, store, boats, caravans, plant and equipment etc. This property is priced to sell so be quick. Inspection strictly by appointment.

Description:
Great Investment with Bay Views
This lovely well presented 2 bedroom unit is situated serenely among nature, approx. 80 minutes from Melbourne CBD. Hidden from view, privately overlooking the bay, this dwelling offers 2 generous sized bedrooms, reverse cycle heating and cooling, a well appointed kitchen, neat bathroom and your own porch with views of the bay.
This unit will appeal to investors as it will be an attractive rental package with estimated rental return of $210.00/week, also suited first home buyer or will make a great weekend getaway retreat.
Low maintenance, new carpet, renovated kitchen & vacant ready to move in - Be quick to call on this one!

Description:
BUILD ON THE FORESHORE
A rare block with direct access to the foreshore where it is possible to build a two story home (stca). At the end of a very quiet court where you can enjoy walks meandering tracks on the foreshore all the way to the jetty. Approximately 926m2, flat and with an amazing view, you won't find better than this for the price. Corinella offers fantastic fishing, a relaxed life style, easy access to Phillip Island and only 45 minutes to Pakenham, 30 inutes to Wonthaggi, 20 minutes to San Remo. A perfect place to retire, semi retire or simply holiday.

Address: 8A Section M, The Centre Way French Island VIC 3921
Description:
CHEAPEST LAND AVAILABLE
BE QUICK!
Entry level opportunity to secure this clear, vacant Land of approx. 1.62ha (4 Acres) centrally located on the Island adjacent to the Perseverance Primary School, approx 5 kms from ferry.
Fully fenced with 7 strand barbed wire, recessed entry and gate on well-maintained road.
Zoned for Farming use with planning permit available for single dwelling (STGA).
Land of this size is rare on the Island and this is an opportunity to purchase at fair value.
Contact Exclusive Agent Phil Bock on 0438 497 715 for inspection, documentation and further details.
Terms 10% Deposit. Balance 60 days. Vacant Possession.

This is a great purchase for your future!!

Description:
FISHERMAN SHACK
Take Notice that this property is a shack in need of repair and is being sold as is. The vendor is looking for an unconditional sale!!!!!!
Featuring 1 bedroom, small kitchen/living area. There is potential to make little getaway weekender. Located within walking distance to water boardwalk and bus service. Close to The Gurdies bush, wineries and small group of shops with cafes, doctor, newsagency and bank. Easy commute to CBD with dual lane highway. Phillip Island and major shopping centre approx.. 25 mins.
We have obtained all information in this document from sources we believe to be reliable. However, we cannot guarantee its accuracy. Prospective purchasers are advised to carry out their own investigations. www.1stre.com.au

Description:
Ship ahoy
Offered here 4 bedroom home with brilliant bay views. Imagine sitting at your dining table enjoying your meal and being able to also enjoy wonderful water views of Westernport Bay and French Island in Corinella. Situated just a short stroll to the 24 hour jetty, this home offers potential with so many extras. Open plan living, country style kitchen and a lovely front verandah perfect for those summer bay breezes and viewing those marvelous bay views. The property offers plenty of access for the boat or caravan with a garage at rear. Priced to sell, be quick for this property.
